    "encrypted": "false",
    "instructions_important": "false",
    "long_instructions": "### Make it Random\r\n\r\nIt's time to add the random element to make your song choose between each of your backing tracks!\r\n\r\n**Do This**:\r\n- Double-check your backing tracks are inside a parent block like `repeat` or `play sequential` or `play together`\r\n- Drag out a `play random` block and put _all_ of your code inside of it\r\n  - Your timeline should update so all of the backing tracks are stacked on top of each other!\r\n- Drag out a `repeat` block and put _all_ if your code inside! Then make the song repeat at least 5 times\r\n  - This gives your song enough time to choose each backting rack a random amount of times\r\n  \r\nRun your code! Each time you press run, it should select a different combination of your backing tracks! Here is an example of what your code could look like inside the `repeat` and `play random` blocks:\r\n\r\n![](https://images.code.org/0f99ecf0ba3a816dd902f1ded001ee94-image-1745529017930.png)",
